<br>
This makes substaing our pet more imperative than ever.<br>
<br>
While chaining pets is viable, it is not as useful if you are equiping pets with proccing weapons, as they will increase your pets efficency, add in armour/muzzles etc.. and the value of substaining one pet rises even higher.<br>
<br>
Also with necros having a 125 mana 1000 point heal on the test server as well as this a poison based DD that will rival our best.<br>
<br>
Neurotoxin    <br>
Decrease Hitpoints by 1260 (L61) to 1300 (L65) <br>
 <br>
Any arguments at least to me why we should be denided a very mana cost effiecent heal spell is null and void.<br>
<br>
Necromancers can DD near as well as we can now, there pets damage output is very close to ours,and with a 1000 point heal, even if a mob isn't feared they can maintain it for very little mana cost. In fact 500 mana buys them 4000 points in heals, About the same hit points as the magician epic pet.<br>
<br>
Now as you know if a necro is fighting undead they also have a 50% slow, that will help their pet tank that much better in their specialized field of the undead.<br>
<br>
With life taps and liche form, mana for a necro is usually never an issue as it is to the soloing mage that wants to keep one fully buffed pet alive (and as said, the new proccing weapons if they go live, is another reason to take that route, though clearly it isn't our only route).<br>
<br>
If the post sounds like class envy, so be it. Though I look at it as trying to keep the magican class alive with options.<br>
<br>
