<br>
1.  Pets in raids and in groups don't usually tank so their defense in those situations is irrelevant.<br>
<br>
2.  Their mana regen is the best in the game and getting better with PoP<br>
<br>
3.  Pet heal is awesome (better than topor) and can be kept up indefinately against a mob since they can tap back health easily for canni'ing more mana.  So their pets can tank effectively IF they so choose.<br>
<br>
4.  Nuke is going to be less resistable being poison based(probably more aggro though) but then they have FD--death peace.<br>
<br>
5.  They can heal, group heal, MW, twitch, FD for CR, Rez, Summon corpse--all very useful in groups and raids.<br>
<br>
6.  Their short term damage will rival ours and their LT damage will blow it away when you factor DoTs.<br>
<br>
7.  Not gonna even mention snare, fear, and mez--oops I did.<br>
<br>
8.  We still have mod rod but all of us (well the great majority it seems) have come to the conclusion that if we are turned into twitch bitches what is the point of playing the classes.<br>
<br>
I'm still hoping to be surprised.<br>
<br>
Someone want to tell me why we are useful again?  I tell you unless we get a very nice present that I don't currently see, I just don't see the point in our class Vs the necro class.  Am I whining?  Probably but I also think I'm looking at this very logically and sizing up all the variables and weighing them out.<br>
