<br>
  Please check the spell before posting. It takes NO health from the necro.  <br>
<br>
  The pet is healed for 1000 hit points for 125 mana. That is it. Here are the details of the spell as shown on Lucy.<br>
<br>
 Touch of Death  Detail | History | Raw Data  <br>
 <br>
  <br>
Slot Description <br>
1:  Increase Hitpoints by 1000 <br>
2:  Decrease Disease Counter by 10 <br>
 <br>
  <br>
Mana: 125 Skill: Alteration <br>
Casting Time: 4.5 Recast Time: 7.5 <br>
Fizzle Time: 2.5 Resist: Unresistable <br>
Range: 100 Location: Any <br>
Time of Day: Any Fizzle Adj 25 <br>
Vendor Sold: No Interruptable: Yes <br>
Target Type: Undead Spell Type: Beneficial <br>
Source: Test 10/10   <br>
 <br>
  <br>
Classes: NEC/64 <br>
Duration: Instant <br>
 <br>
  <br>
Cast on other: Someone bones begin to regrow. <br>
 <br>
So in 4.5 seconds the pet is healed for 1000 points. <br>
7.5 seconds later they can cast it again.<br>
<br>
Nowhere do you see the necro losing 1 hit point let alone 500.<br>
<br>
Not that a 500 hit point loss to a necro is a problem with life taps and Heal over time dots etc.. except this new heal doesn't require taking any hit points from the Necro.<br>
<br>
Also their new DD spell casts in 6 seconds with a 4 second refresh timer.<br>
<br>
That is not a huge recast penalty, and a necro will just cast a life tap if needed during that time interval, or land another dot, or heal there pet etc...<br>
<br>
As for their &quot;ol&quot; pets having less hit points, on a raid there pet takes no melee damage as the MT soaks that up.<br>
<br>
True the AOE's will hit it, though for 125 mana 1000 hit points are restored, and we heal on average 580 or so for 275 mana.<br>
<br>
Sorry the numbers do not add up. They will be able to keep their pet alive, nuke for 1300 + damage, land 1000's of points worth of dots on every mob, though on shorter fights I see them nuking and life tap mainly.<br>
<br>
In any event I was not missing a lot of information. It is correct as I type this.<br>
<br>
125 mana. 1000 point heal. NO LOSS of hit points to the necro.<br>
<br>
Their new DD spell 465 mana 1300 damage 6 second casting time and 4 second re-cast times.<br>
<br>
For a class that Direct Damage was never there specialty this is a huge increase in DD spells. <br>
<br>
